OL,3,CMark Drakeford says 'scars' of 1984
OL,4,Cminers' strike 'live on' 40 years later
OL,6,FSpeaking of his own memories of the ,
OL,7,Fas a probation officer sent to observe
OL,8,Fthe pickets, he said: "They are
OL,9,Fabsolutely vivid in my mind, the
OL,10,Fmemories of standing there and
OL,11,Fwatching what was happening and
OL,12,Fwriting reports about it afterwards.
OL,14,F"The strength of feeling was such that
OL,15,FI think the first thing to say is that
OL,16,Fyou recognise that the scars live on.
OL,18,F"You hope, of course, that the scars
OL,19,Fwill heal and people will find a way
OL,20,Fto reconciliation.
